NAME: postgres
LAST DEPLOYED: Tue Nov 22 11:06:34 2022
NAMESPACE: csdm
STATUS: deployed
REVISION: 1
TEST SUITE: None
NOTES:
** Please be patient while the chart is being deployed **

PostgreSQL can be accessed via port 5432 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:

    postgres-postgresql.csdm.svc.cluster.local - Read/Write connection

To get the password for "postgres" run:

    export POSTGRES_ADMIN_PASSWORD=$(kubectl get secret --namespace csdm postgres-postgresql -o jsonpath="{.data.postgresql-postgres-password}" | base64 --decode)

To get the password for "bn_keycloak" run:

    export POSTGRES_PASSWORD=$(kubectl get secret --namespace csdm postgres-postgresql -o jsonpath="{.data.postgresql-password}" | base64 --decode)

To connect to your database run the following command:

    kubectl run postgres-postgresql-client --rm --tty -i --restart='Never' --namespace csdm --image docker.io/bitnami/postgresql:11.12.0-debian-10-r23 --env="PGPASSWORD=$POSTGRES_PASSWORD" --command -- psql --host postgres-postgresql -U bn_keycloak -d postgres -p 5432



To connect to your database from outside the cluster execute the following commands:

    kubectl port-forward --namespace csdm svc/postgres-postgresql 5432:5432 &
    PGPASSWORD="$POSTGRES_PASSWORD" psql --host 127.0.0.1 -U bn_keycloak -d postgres -p 5432
