** Please be patient while the chart is being deployed **

Keycloak can be accessed through the following DNS name from within your cluster:

    csdm-keycloak.csdm.svc.cluster.local (port 8080)

To access Keycloak from outside the cluster execute the following commands:

1. Get the Keycloak URL by running these commands:

    export HTTP_SERVICE_PORT=$(kubectl get --namespace csdm -o jsonpath="{.spec.ports[?(@.name=='http')].port}" services csdm-keycloak)
    kubectl port-forward --namespace csdm svc/csdm-keycloak ${HTTP_SERVICE_PORT}:${HTTP_SERVICE_PORT} ${HTTPS_SERVICE_PORT}:${HTTPS_SERVICE_PORT} &

    echo "http://127.0.0.1:${HTTP_SERVICE_PORT}/"

2. Access Keycloak using the obtained URL.
