ZooKeeper can be accessed via port 2181 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:

    csdm-zookeeper.csdm.svc.cluster.local

To connect to your ZooKeeper server run the following commands:

    export POD_NAME=$(kubectl get pods --namespace csdm -l "app.kubernetes.io/name=zookeeper,app.kubernetes.io/instance=csdm-zookeeper,app.kubernetes.io/component=zookeeper" -o jsonpath="{.items[0].metadata.name}")
    kubectl exec -it $POD_NAME -- zkCli.sh

To connect to your ZooKeeper server from outside the cluster execute the following commands:

    kubectl port-forward --namespace csdm svc/csdm-zookeeper 2181:2181 &
    zkCli.sh 127.0.0.1:2181
