Redis(TM) can be accessed on the following DNS names from within your cluster:

    csdm-redis-master.csdm.svc.cluster.local for read/write operations (port 6379)
    csdm-redis-replicas.csdm.svc.cluster.local for read-only operations (port 6379)



To connect to your Redis(TM) server:

1. Run a Redis(TM) pod that you can use as a client:

   kubectl run --namespace csdm redis-client --restart='Never'  --image docker.io/bitnami/redis:6.2.4-debian-10-r0 --command -- sleep infinity

   Use the following command to attach to the pod:

   kubectl exec --tty -i redis-client \
   --namespace csdm -- bash

2. Connect using the Redis(TM) CLI:
   redis-cli -h csdm-redis-master
   redis-cli -h csdm-redis-replicas

To connect to your database from outside the cluster execute the following commands:

    kubectl port-forward --namespace csdm svc/csdm-redis-master 6379:6379 &
    redis-cli -h 127.0.0.1 -p 6379
